# Testing Standards

## Setup
- `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, `asyncio_mode = "auto"`
- Shared fixtures in `tests/conftest.py` (project_root, settings, clean_env)

## Patterns
- Use `@pytest.fixture` for reusable setup
- Use `pytest.mark.asyncio` for async tests (or rely on asyncio_mode)
- Mock external APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI, ElevenLabs) in unit tests
- Use `pytest.mark.integration` for tests that hit real services
- Use `pytest.mark.slow` for expensive tests

## Structure
- Unit: `tests/unit/test_<module>.py`
- Integration: `tests/integration/test_pipeline.py`
- Contracts: `tests/contracts/test_mcp_server.py` (MCP tool schema)

## Naming
- Test functions: `test_<behavior>_<condition>` (e.g. `test_transcribe_returns_empty_on_silence`)
